{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αἵρεσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <b>taking</b>, especially of a town, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.1, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ βασιλέος αἵ. <b>the taking by</b> the king, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 9.3; ἐλπίζων ταχίστην -σιν ἔσεσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.75\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἵ. δυνάμεως <b>acquisition</b> of power, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 513a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—generally, <b>taking, receiving</b>, ἐπιγενημάτων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 27.66 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> (αἱρέομαι) <b>choice</b>, αἵρεσίν τ᾽ ἐμοὶ δίδου[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 779; τῶνδε.. αἵρεσιν παρδίδωμι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 10.82\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; followed by <i>relative</i>, αἵ. διδόναι ὁκοτέρην.., εἰ.., etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.11, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 22.19\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἵ. προτιθέναι, προβάλλειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 196c, “Sph.” 245b; εἰ νέμοι τις αἵρεσιν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 265; αἵρεσιν λαβεῖν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 36.11; ποιεῖσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7.19; αἵ. γίγνεταί τινι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.61\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐκ ἔχει αἵρεσιν it admits no <b>choice</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.708b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.2</b></Level3> <b>choice, election</b> of magistrates, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.89, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1266a26, +others; αἱρέσει, opposed to κλήρῳ, 1300a19, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.3</b></Level3> <b>inclination, choice</b>, πρός τινα Philipp. cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.166, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 2.61.9, etc., compare “IG” 2.591b\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to φυγή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 3p.62U.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; περὶ αἱρέσεων καὶ φυγῶν, title of treatise by Epicurus. <br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> <b>purpose, course of action</b> or <b>thought</b>, like{προαίρεσις}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 256c; ἡ αἵ. τῆς πρεσβείας 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.11\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἵ. Ἐλληνική <b>the study</b> of Greek literature, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 39.1.3\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]:—<b>conduct,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTeb. 28.10 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.2</b></Level3> <b>system of philosophic principles</b>, or <b>those who profess such principles, sect, school</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.93.8, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.29, Polystr. p.20 W., 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “Amm.” 1.7, “Comp.” 2, +others, compare 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Familiares” 15.16.3\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; κατὰ τῶν αἱ., title of treatise by Antipater of Tarsus; περὶ αἱρέσεων, title of Menippean satire by Varro,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare “fragment” 164\">Refs</a>]; αἵρεσις πρὸς Γοργιππίδην, title of work by Chrysippus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 7.191\">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; especially <b>religious party</b> or <b>sect</b>, of the Essenes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 2.8.1; the Sadducees and Pharisees, NT.Act.5.17, 15.5, 26.5; the Christians, [prev. work] 24.5, 14, 28.22\">NT+1st c.AD+</a>], generally, <b>faction, party</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Bella Civilia” 5.2. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.3</b></Level3> <b>corps</b> of epheboi, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “OGI” 176 (from Egypt). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.4</b></Level3> Astrology texts, <b>'condition'</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Ptolemaeus Mathematicus “Tetrabiblos” 21; ἡ ἡμερινὴ αἵ. Vett. Val. 1.13. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.III</b></Level2> <b>proposed condition, proposal</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 3.10. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.III.2</b></Level3> <b>commission</b>, ἡ ἐπὶ τοὺς νέους αἵ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Axiochus” 367a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>embassy, mission,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 4.937 (Epid.). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.III.3</b></Level3> <b>freewill offering</b>, opposed to <b>vow</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.22.18, +others \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.III.4</b></Level3> <b>bid</b> at auction, τὴν ἀμείνονα αἵ. διδόντι παραδοθῆναι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 716.22 (2nd c.AD), compare 1630.8 (3rd c.AD).\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0139","accentedUnicode":"αἵρεσις","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0138","matchingForm":"αἱρέω","stepTransliteration":"haireō","gloss":"to choose","_zh_tw_Gloss":"選擇","_es_Gloss":"escoger","_zh_Gloss":"选择"},{"strongNumber":"G0140","matchingForm":"αἱρετίζω","stepTransliteration":"hairetizō","gloss":"to choose","_zh_tw_Gloss":"揀選","_es_Gloss":"elegir","_zh_Gloss":"拣选"},{"strongNumber":"G0141","matchingForm":"αἱρετικός","stepTransliteration":"hairetikos","gloss":"schismatic","_zh_tw_Gloss":"分門結黨","_es_Gloss":"que causa divisiones","_zh_Gloss":"分门结党"},{"strongNumber":"G0830","matchingForm":"αὐθαίρετος","stepTransliteration":"authairetos","gloss":"self-chosen","_zh_tw_Gloss":"是甘心樂意, 自願","_es_Gloss":"de su voluntad","_zh_Gloss":"是甘心乐意, 自愿"},{"strongNumber":"G4255","matchingForm":"προαιρέω","stepTransliteration":"proaireō","gloss":"to predetermine","_zh_tw_Gloss":"所酌定","_es_Gloss":"predeterminar","_zh_Gloss":"所酌定"},{"strongNumber":"G4400","matchingForm":"προχειρίζω","stepTransliteration":"procheirizō","gloss":"to appoint","_zh_tw_Gloss":"揀選了","_es_Gloss":"designar","_zh_Gloss":"拣选了"},{"strongNumber":"G4401","matchingForm":"προχειροτονέω","stepTransliteration":"procheirotoneō","gloss":"to choose","_zh_tw_Gloss":"預先所揀選","_es_Gloss":"elegir","_zh_Gloss":"预先所拣选"}],"shortDef":"sect (religious party), faction, heresy","mediumDef":"strictly, <b>a choice</b> or <b>option;</b> hence, <b>a religious sect, faction;</b> by implication, <b>discord, contention, heresy</b>","stepGloss":"sect","stepTransliteration":"hairesis","count":9,"_es_Definition":"partido religioso  división, facción; enseñanza o partido falso","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 遵循某個共同的教義或宗旨原則的群體(教派或黨派)<br> 1a) 撒都該人(猶太教派之一, 不信有復活)<br> 1b) 異端<br> 1c) 歧見,分裂(林前 11:19; 加 5:20)<br>5) 看法,教條(彼後 2:1)","_zh_Definition":"1) 遵循某个共同的教义或宗旨原则的群体(教派或党派)<br> 1a) 撒都该人(犹太教派之一, 不信有复活)<br> 1b) 异端<br> 1c) 歧见,分裂(林前11:19; 加5:20)<br>5) 看法,教条(彼后2:1)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"giáo phái ; phái ; phe đảng ; sự chia rẻ, một dị giáo","_zh_tw_Gloss":"教派, 異端","_es_Gloss":"secta","_zh_Gloss":"教派, 异端"}]}